The paper discusses a theoretical framework for autonomous agents operating in dynamic environments, which involves making inferences and selecting optimal behaviors based on a generative model. This is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the focus on modeling and optimization, cs.AI and cs.NE are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.RO, and cs.SY.
